  "warnings": [
    "Do not damage the\nsealing surfaces.",
    "24.  \nDetach the timing case (4).\n \n\n\n\n•  \n11 bolts (1) and (5)\n \n\n\n\n\n\n•  \nRemove the gasket (2).\n Note:   Cover the opening\n(3) in the timing case with a cloth.\n \n\n\n\n\n\n•  \nUse a suitable tool to remove the oil seal.\n \n\n\n\n\n\nDo not damage the\nsealing surfaces.\n \n\n\n\n•  \nClean the sealing surfaces.",
    "Note the\nidentification marking (2) – do not mix up.",
    "41.  \nInstall the balancer shaft on the intake side.\n \n\n\n\nNote the\nidentification marking (2) – do not mix up.\n \n\n\n\n•  \nCoat the sliding surfaces with engine oil.\n \n\n\n\n\n\n•  \nTightening torque 9 Nm \n \n\n\n\n\n\n•  \nRotate the balancer shaft once (check for ease of\nmovement).",
    "Note the\nidentification marking (1) – do not mix up.",
    "42.  \nInstall the balancer shaft on the exhaust side.\n \n\n\n\nNote the\nidentification marking (1) – do not mix up.\n \n\n\n\n•  \nCoat the sliding surfaces with engine oil.\n \n\n\n\n\n\n•  \nTightening torque 9 Nm \n \n\n\n\n\n\n•  \nRotate the balancer shaft once (check for ease of\nmovement).",
    "The TDC reference\npoints on the timing chain are indicated by coloured links in the\nchain. These must line up with the markings on the timing\nsprockets.",
    "43.  \nInstall the balancer shaft timing chain.\n \n\n\n\nThe TDC reference\npoints on the timing chain are indicated by coloured links in the\nchain. These must line up with the markings on the timing\nsprockets.\n \n\n\n\n•  \nLay the timing chain in place.\n \n\n\n\n–\nChain link (2) (copper coloured) to the marking on the balancer\nshaft on the intake side of the engine.\n \n\n\n\n\n\n–\nSecure the chain link (3) with a plastic wedge at the marking\non the balancer shaft timing chain sprocket.\n \n\n\n\n\n\n–\nChain onto coolant pump sprocket\n \n\n\n\n\n\n–\nChain link (1) to the marking on the balancer shaft on the\nexhaust side of the engine.",
    "After a single\nrevolution of the engine the TDC markings will no longer line up\nwith the coloured chain links.",
    "46.  \nInstall the balancer shaft timing chain tensioner.\n \n\n\n\n•  \nLock the chain tensioner (1) with KM-6077 .\n \n\n\n\n–\nRotate the piston clockwise, press it in and insert KM-6077 into the designated bores.\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n•  \nTightening torque 10 Nm \n \n\n\n\n\n\n•  \nTake out KM-6077 .\n \n\n\n\n\n\nAfter a single\nrevolution of the engine the TDC markings will no longer line up\nwith the coloured chain links.\n \n\n\n\n•  \nIf the TDC markings no longer line up with the coloured chain\nlinks – refit the camshaft timing chain.",
    "49.  \nFit the camshaft timing chain.\n \n\n\n\nThe TDC reference\npoints on the timing chain are indicated by coloured links in the\nchain. These must line up with the markings on the timing\nsprockets.\n \n\n\n\n•  \nChain link (copper colour) (1) to INT marking (2) on the intake\ncamshaft sprocket",
    "Check that the TDC\nreference points line up.",
    "52.  \nSecure the camshaft timing chain.\n \n\n\n\nCheck that the TDC\nreference points line up.\n \n\n\n\n•  \nSecure the chain link (1) with a plastic wedge at the marking\non the camshaft timing chain sprocket",
    "53.  \nInstall the exhaust camshaft sprocket.\n \n\n\n\nCheck that the TDC\nreference points line up.\n \n\n\n\n•  \nChain link (1) to EXH marking (2) on the exhaust camshaft\nsprocket\n \n\n\n\n\n\n•  \nRotate the exhaust camshaft by the hexagon until the exhaust\ncamshaft sprocket is seated in the guide.\n \n\n\n\n\n\n•  \nUse a new bolt.\n \n\n\n\n\n\n•  \nHold the camshaft by the hexagon.\n \n\n\n\n–\nTightening torque 85 Nm + 30° +\n15°",
    "Failure to follow this\ninstruction could cause the camshaft timing chain to jump.",
    "The knock sensor must\nmake full contact with the cylinder block across its entire contact\nsurface – ensure utmost cleanliness. Make sure that the\ntightening torque is exactly as specified.",
    "70.  \nInstall the knock sensor.\n \n\n\n\nThe knock sensor must\nmake full contact with the cylinder block across its entire contact\nsurface – ensure utmost cleanliness. Make sure that the\ntightening torque is exactly as specified.\n \n\n\n\n•  \nTightening torque 23 Nm \n \n\n\n\n\n\n•  \nAttach the wiring harness connector."
